ening them up to debate as crucial social concerns. Written by leading international experts in the field, this is a must-read for anyone interested in contemporary ethnic inequalities and racism, from academics and policy makers to voluntary and community sector organisations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDiscriminationzGreat BritainvStatistics. 0aRacismzGreat BritainvStatistics. 0aSocial stratificationzGreat BritainvStatistics. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aAparicio-Castro, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBegum, Neema, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorkowska, Magda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBécares, Laia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBécares, Laia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aClark, Ken, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEllingworth, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinney, Nissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinney, Nissa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarrison, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaycox, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKapadia, Dharmi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKapadia, Dharmi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoretti, Angelo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l